450struct yy_buffer_state
451 {
452 FILE *yy_input_file;
453
454 char *yy_ch_buf; /* input buffer */
455 char *yy_buf_pos; /* current position in input buffer */
456
457 /* Size of input buffer in bytes, not including room for EOB

460 size_t yy_buf_size;

464 */

466
467 /* Whether we "own" the buffer - i.e., we know we created it,
468 * and can realloc() it to grow it, and should free() it to
469 * delete it.
470 */
471 int yy_is_our_buffer;
472
473 /* Whether this is an "interactive" input source; if so, and
474 * if we're using stdio for input, then we want to use getc()
475 * instead of fread(), to make sure we stop fetching input after
476 * each newline.
477 */
478 int yy_is_interactive;
479
480 /* Whether we're considered to be at the beginning of a line.
481 * If so, '^' rules will be active on the next match, otherwise
482 * not.
483 */
484 int yy_at_bol;
485
486 int yy_bs_lineno; /**< The line count. */
487 int yy_bs_column; /**< The column count. */
488
489 /* Whether to try to fill the input buffer when we reach the
490 * end of it.
491 */
492 int yy_fill_buffer;
493
494 int yy_buffer_status;
495
496#define YY_BUFFER_NEW 0
497#define YY_BUFFER_NORMAL 1
498 /* When an EOF's been seen but there's still some text to process
499 * then we mark the buffer as YY_EOF_PENDING, to indicate that we
500 * shouldn't try reading from the input source any more. We might
501 * still have a bunch of tokens to match, though, because of
502 * possible backing-up.
503 *
504 * When we actually see the EOF, we change the status to "new"
505 * (via yyrestart()), so that the user can continue scanning by
506 * just pointing yyin at a new input file.
507 */
508#define YY_BUFFER_EOF_PENDING 2
509
510 };

1386 for ( i = 0; i < number_to_move; ++i )
1387 *(dest++) = *(source++);
1388
1389 if ( YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_buffer_status == YY_BUFFER_EOF_PENDING )
1390 /* don't do the read, it's not guaranteed to return an EOF,
1391 * just force an EOF
1392 */
1393 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_n_chars = (yy_n_chars) = 0;
1394
1395 else
1396 {
1397 yy_size_t num_to_read =
1398 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_buf_size - number_to_move - 1;
1399
1400 while ( num_to_read <= 0 )
1401 { /* Not enough room in the buffer - grow it. */
1402
1403 /* just a shorter name for the current buffer */
1404 YY_BUFFER_STATE b = YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE;
1405
1406 int yy_c_buf_p_offset =
1407 (int) ((yy_c_buf_p) - b->yy_ch_buf);
1408
1409 if ( b->yy_is_our_buffer )
1410 {
1411 yy_size_t new_size = b->yy_buf_size * 2;
1412
1413 if ( new_size <= 0 )
1414 b->yy_buf_size += b->yy_buf_size / 8;
1415 else
1416 b->yy_buf_size *= 2;
1417
1418 b->yy_ch_buf = (char *)
1419 /* Include room in for 2 EOB chars. */
1420 yyrealloc( (void *) b->yy_ch_buf,
1421 (yy_size_t) (b->yy_buf_size + 2) );
1422 }
1423 else
1424 /* Can't grow it, we don't own it. */
1425 b->yy_ch_buf = NULL;
1426
1427 if ( ! b->yy_ch_buf )
1428 YY_FATAL_ERROR(
1429 "fatal error - scanner input buffer overflow" );
1430
1431 (yy_c_buf_p) = &b->yy_ch_buf[yy_c_buf_p_offset];
1432
1433 num_to_read = YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_buf_size -
1434 number_to_move - 1;
1435
1436 }
1437
1438 if ( num_to_read > YY_READ_BUF_SIZE )
1439 num_to_read = YY_READ_BUF_SIZE;
1440
1441 /* Read in more data. */
1442 YY_INPUT( (&YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf[number_to_move]),
1443 (yy_n_chars), num_to_read );
1444
1445 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_n_chars = (yy_n_chars);
1446 }
1447
1448 if ( (yy_n_chars) == 0 )
1449 {
1450 if ( number_to_move == YY_MORE_ADJ )
1451 {
1452 ret_val = EOB_ACT_END_OF_FILE;
1453 yyrestart( yyin );
1454 }
1455
1456 else
1457 {
1458 ret_val = EOB_ACT_LAST_MATCH;
1459 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_buffer_status =
1460 YY_BUFFER_EOF_PENDING;
1461 }
1462 }
1463
1464 else
1465 ret_val = EOB_ACT_CONTINUE_SCAN;
1466
1467 if (((yy_n_chars) + number_to_move) > YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_buf_size) {
1468 /* Extend the array by 50%, plus the number we really need. */
1469 yy_size_t new_size = (yy_n_chars) + number_to_move + ((yy_n_chars) >> 1);
1470 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf = (char *) yyrealloc(
1471 (void *) YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf, (yy_size_t) new_size );
1472 if ( ! YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf )
1473 YY_FATAL_ERROR( "out of dynamic memory in yy_get_next_buffer()" );
1474 /* "- 2" to take care of EOB's */
1475 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_buf_size = (yy_size_t) (new_size - 2);
1476 }
1477
1478 (yy_n_chars) += number_to_move;
1479 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf[(yy_n_chars)] = YY_END_OF_BUFFER_CHAR;
1480 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf[(yy_n_chars) + 1] = YY_END_OF_BUFFER_CHAR;
1481
1482 (yytext_ptr) = &YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf[0];
1483
1484 return ret_val;
1485}

1487/* yy_get_previous_state - get the state just before the EOB char was reached */
1488
1489 static yy_state_type yy_get_previous_state (void)
1490{
1491 yy_state_type yy_current_state;
1492 char *yy_cp;
1493
1494 yy_current_state = (yy_start);
1495
1496 for ( yy_cp = (yytext_ptr) + YY_MORE_ADJ; yy_cp < (yy_c_buf_p); ++yy_cp )
1497 {
1498 YY_CHAR yy_c = (*yy_cp ? yy_ec[YY_SC_TO_UI(*yy_cp)] : 1);
1499 if ( yy_accept[yy_current_state] )
1500 {
1501 (yy_last_accepting_state) = yy_current_state;
1502 (yy_last_accepting_cpos) = yy_cp;
1503 }
1504 while ( yy_chk[yy_base[yy_current_state] + yy_c] != yy_current_state )
1505 {
1506 yy_current_state = (int) yy_def[yy_current_state];
1507 if ( yy_current_state >= 40 )
1508 yy_c = yy_meta[yy_c];
1509 }
1510 yy_current_state = yy_nxt[yy_base[yy_current_state] + yy_c];
1511 }
1512
1513 return yy_current_state;
1514}

1516/* yy_try_NUL_trans - try to make a transition on the NUL character
1517 *
1518 * synopsis
1519 * next_state = yy_try_NUL_trans( current_state );
1520 */
1521 static yy_state_type yy_try_NUL_trans (yy_state_type yy_current_state )
1522{
1523 int yy_is_jam;
1524 char *yy_cp = (yy_c_buf_p);
1525
1526 YY_CHAR yy_c = 1;
1527 if ( yy_accept[yy_current_state] )
1528 {
1529 (yy_last_accepting_state) = yy_current_state;
1530 (yy_last_accepting_cpos) = yy_cp;
1531 }
1532 while ( yy_chk[yy_base[yy_current_state] + yy_c] != yy_current_state )
1533 {
1534 yy_current_state = (int) yy_def[yy_current_state];
1535 if ( yy_current_state >= 40 )
1536 yy_c = yy_meta[yy_c];
1537 }
1538 yy_current_state = yy_nxt[yy_base[yy_current_state] + yy_c];
1539 yy_is_jam = (yy_current_state == 39);
1540
1541 return yy_is_jam ? 0 : yy_current_state;
1542}

1559
1560 if ( *(yy_c_buf_p) == YY_END_OF_BUFFER_CHAR )
1561 {

1563 * If this occurs *before* the EOB characters, then it's a
1564 * valid NUL; if not, then we've hit the end of the buffer.
1565 */

1569

1573 ++(yy_c_buf_p);

1576 {
1577 case EOB_ACT_LAST_MATCH:

1579 * sees that we've accumulated a
1580 * token and flags that we need to
1581 * try matching the token before
1582 * proceeding. But for input(),
1583 * there's no matching to consider.
1584 * So convert the EOB_ACT_LAST_MATCH
1585 * to EOB_ACT_END_OF_FILE.
1586 */

1590
1591 /*FALLTHROUGH*/
1592
1593 case EOB_ACT_END_OF_FILE:

1607 case EOB_ACT_CONTINUE_SCAN:

1609 break;
1610 }
1611 }
1612 }
1613
1614 c = *(unsigned char *) (yy_c_buf_p); /* cast for 8-bit char's */
1615 *(yy_c_buf_p) = '\0'; /* preserve yytext */
1616 (yy_hold_char) = *++(yy_c_buf_p);
1617
1618 return c;

1640/** Switch to a different input buffer.
1641 * @param new_buffer The new input buffer.
1642 *
1643 */
1644 void yy_switch_to_buffer (YY_BUFFER_STATE new_buffer )
1645{
1646
1647 /* TODO. We should be able to replace this entire function body
1648 * with
1649 * yypop_buffer_state();
1650 * yypush_buffer_state(new_buffer);
1651 */
1652 yyensure_buffer_stack ();
1653 if ( YY_CURRENT_BUFFER == new_buffer )
1654 return;
1655
1656 if ( YY_CURRENT_BUFFER )
1657 {
1658 /* Flush out information for old buffer. */
1659 *(yy_c_buf_p) = (yy_hold_char);
1660 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_buf_pos = (yy_c_buf_p);
1661 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_n_chars = (yy_n_chars);

1668 * EOF (yywrap()) processing, but the only time this flag
1669 * is looked at is after yywrap() is called, so it's safe
1670 * to go ahead and always set it.
1671 */
1672 (yy_did_buffer_switch_on_eof) = 1;

1678 (yytext_ptr) = (yy_c_buf_p) = YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_buf_pos;

1683/** Allocate and initialize an input buffer state.
1684 * @param file A readable stream.
1685 * @param size The character buffer size in bytes. When in doubt, use @c YY_BUF_SIZE.
1686 *
1687 * @return the allocated buffer state.
1688 */
1689 YY_BUFFER_STATE yy_create_buffer (FILE * file, yy_size_t size )
1690{
1691 YY_BUFFER_STATE b;
1692
1693 b = (YY_BUFFER_STATE) yyalloc( sizeof( struct yy_buffer_state ) );
1694 if ( ! b )
1695 YY_FATAL_ERROR( "out of dynamic memory in yy_create_buffer()" );
1696
1697 b->yy_buf_size = size;
1698
1699 /* yy_ch_buf has to be 2 characters longer than the size given because
1700 * we need to put in 2 end-of-buffer characters.
1701 */
1702 b->yy_ch_buf = (char *) yyalloc( (yy_size_t) (b->yy_buf_size + 2) );
1703 if ( ! b->yy_ch_buf )
1704 YY_FATAL_ERROR( "out of dynamic memory in yy_create_buffer()" );
1705
1706 b->yy_is_our_buffer = 1;
1707
1708 yy_init_buffer( b, file );
1709
1710 return b;
1711}

1713/** Destroy the buffer.
1714 * @param b a buffer created with yy_create_buffer()
1715 *
1716 */
1717 void yy_delete_buffer (YY_BUFFER_STATE b )
1718{
1719
1720 if ( ! b )
1721 return;
1722
1723 if ( b == YY_CURRENT_BUFFER ) /* Not sure if we should pop here. */
1724 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE = (YY_BUFFER_STATE) 0;
1725
1726 if ( b->yy_is_our_buffer )
1727 yyfree( (void *) b->yy_ch_buf );
1728
1729 yyfree( (void *) b );
1730}

1732/* Initializes or reinitializes a buffer.
1733 * This function is sometimes called more than once on the same buffer,
1734 * such as during a yyrestart() or at EOF.
1735 */
1736 static void yy_init_buffer (YY_BUFFER_STATE b, FILE * file )
1737
1738{
1739 int oerrno = errno;
1740
1741 yy_flush_buffer( b );
1742
1743 b->yy_input_file = file;
1744 b->yy_fill_buffer = 1;
1745
1746 /* If b is the current buffer, then yy_init_buffer was _probably_
1747 * called from yyrestart() or through yy_get_next_buffer.
1748 * In that case, we don't want to reset the lineno or column.
1749 */
1750 if (b != YY_CURRENT_BUFFER){
1751 b->yy_bs_lineno = 1;
1752 b->yy_bs_column = 0;
1753 }
1754
1755 b->yy_is_interactive = file ? (isatty( fileno(file) ) > 0) : 0;
1756
1757 errno = oerrno;
1758}

1760/** Discard all buffered characters. On the next scan, YY_INPUT will be called.
1761 * @param b the buffer state to be flushed, usually @c YY_CURRENT_BUFFER.
1762 *
1763 */
1764 void yy_flush_buffer (YY_BUFFER_STATE b )
1765{
1766 if ( ! b )
1767 return;
1768
1769 b->yy_n_chars = 0;
1770
1771 /* We always need two end-of-buffer characters. The first causes
1772 * a transition to the end-of-buffer state. The second causes
1773 * a jam in that state.
1774 */
1775 b->yy_ch_buf[0] = YY_END_OF_BUFFER_CHAR;
1776 b->yy_ch_buf[1] = YY_END_OF_BUFFER_CHAR;
1777
1778 b->yy_buf_pos = &b->yy_ch_buf[0];
1779
1780 b->yy_at_bol = 1;
1781 b->yy_buffer_status = YY_BUFFER_NEW;
1782
1783 if ( b == YY_CURRENT_BUFFER )
1784 yy_load_buffer_state( );
1785}

1787/** Pushes the new state onto the stack. The new state becomes
1788 * the current state. This function will allocate the stack
1789 * if necessary.
1790 * @param new_buffer The new state.
1791 *
1792 */
1793void yypush_buffer_state (YY_BUFFER_STATE new_buffer )
1794{
1795 if (new_buffer == NULL)
1796 return;
1797
1798 yyensure_buffer_stack();
1799
1800 /* This block is copied from yy_switch_to_buffer. */
1801 if ( YY_CURRENT_BUFFER )
1802 {
1803 /* Flush out information for old buffer. */
1804 *(yy_c_buf_p) = (yy_hold_char);
1805 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_buf_pos = (yy_c_buf_p);
1806 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_n_chars = (yy_n_chars);
1807 }
1808
1809 /* Only push if top exists. Otherwise, replace top. */
1810 if (YY_CURRENT_BUFFER)
1811 (yy_buffer_stack_top)++;
1812 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE = new_buffer;
1813
1814 /* copied from yy_switch_to_buffer. */
1815 yy_load_buffer_state( );
1816 (yy_did_buffer_switch_on_eof) = 1;
1817}

1819/** Removes and deletes the top of the stack, if present.
1820 * The next element becomes the new top.
1821 *
1822 */
1823void yypop_buffer_state (void)
1824{
1825 if (!YY_CURRENT_BUFFER)
1826 return;
1827
1828 yy_delete_buffer(YY_CURRENT_BUFFER );
1829 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE = NULL;
1830 if ((yy_buffer_stack_top) > 0)
1831 --(yy_buffer_stack_top);
1832
1833 if (YY_CURRENT_BUFFER) {
1834 yy_load_buffer_state( );
1835 (yy_did_buffer_switch_on_eof) = 1;
1836 }
1837}

1839/* Allocates the stack if it does not exist.
1840 * Guarantees space for at least one push.
1841 */
1842static void yyensure_buffer_stack (void)
1843{
1844 yy_size_t num_to_alloc;
1845
1846 if (!(yy_buffer_stack)) {
1847
1848 /* First allocation is just for 2 elements, since we don't know if this
1849 * scanner will even need a stack. We use 2 instead of 1 to avoid an
1850 * immediate realloc on the next call.
1851 */
1852 num_to_alloc = 1; /* After all that talk, this was set to 1 anyways... */
1853 (yy_buffer_stack) = (struct yy_buffer_state**)yyalloc
1854 (num_to_alloc * sizeof(struct yy_buffer_state*)
1855 );
1856 if ( ! (yy_buffer_stack) )
1857 YY_FATAL_ERROR( "out of dynamic memory in yyensure_buffer_stack()" );
1858
1859 memset((yy_buffer_stack), 0, num_to_alloc * sizeof(struct yy_buffer_state*));
1860
1861 (yy_buffer_stack_max) = num_to_alloc;
1862 (yy_buffer_stack_top) = 0;
1863 return;
1864 }
1865
1866 if ((yy_buffer_stack_top) >= ((yy_buffer_stack_max)) - 1){
1867
1868 /* Increase the buffer to prepare for a possible push. */
1869 yy_size_t grow_size = 8 /* arbitrary grow size */;
1870
1871 num_to_alloc = (yy_buffer_stack_max) + grow_size;
1872 (yy_buffer_stack) = (struct yy_buffer_state**)yyrealloc
1873 ((yy_buffer_stack),
1874 num_to_alloc * sizeof(struct yy_buffer_state*)
1875 );
1876 if ( ! (yy_buffer_stack) )
1877 YY_FATAL_ERROR( "out of dynamic memory in yyensure_buffer_stack()" );
1878
1879 /* zero only the new slots.*/
1880 memset((yy_buffer_stack) + (yy_buffer_stack_max), 0, grow_size * sizeof(struct yy_buffer_state*));
1881 (yy_buffer_stack_max) = num_to_alloc;
1882 }
1883}

1885/** Setup the input buffer state to scan directly from a user-specified character buffer.
1886 * @param base the character buffer
1887 * @param size the size in bytes of the character buffer
1888 *
1889 * @return the newly allocated buffer state object.
1890 */
1891YY_BUFFER_STATE yy_scan_buffer (char * base, yy_size_t size )
1892{
1893 YY_BUFFER_STATE b;
1894
1895 if ( size < 2 ||
1896 base[size-2] != YY_END_OF_BUFFER_CHAR ||
1897 base[size-1] != YY_END_OF_BUFFER_CHAR )
1898 /* They forgot to leave room for the EOB's. */
1899 return NULL;
1900
1901 b = (YY_BUFFER_STATE) yyalloc( sizeof( struct yy_buffer_state ) );
1902 if ( ! b )
1903 YY_FATAL_ERROR( "out of dynamic memory in yy_scan_buffer()" );
1904
1905 b->yy_buf_size = (size - 2); /* "- 2" to take care of EOB's */
1906 b->yy_buf_pos = b->yy_ch_buf = base;
1907 b->yy_is_our_buffer = 0;
1908 b->yy_input_file = NULL;
1909 b->yy_n_chars = b->yy_buf_size;
1910 b->yy_is_interactive = 0;
1911 b->yy_at_bol = 1;
1912 b->yy_fill_buffer = 0;
1913 b->yy_buffer_status = YY_BUFFER_NEW;
1914
1915 yy_switch_to_buffer( b );
1916
1917 return b;
1918}

1925 * @note If you want to scan bytes that may contain NUL values, then use
1926 * yy_scan_bytes() instead.

1934/** Setup the input buffer state to scan the given bytes. The next call to yylex() will
1935 * scan from a @e copy of @a bytes.
1936 * @param yybytes the byte buffer to scan
1937 * @param _yybytes_len the number of bytes in the buffer pointed to by @a bytes.
1938 *
1939 * @return the newly allocated buffer state object.
1940 */
1941YY_BUFFER_STATE yy_scan_bytes (const char * yybytes, yy_size_t _yybytes_len )
1942{
1943 YY_BUFFER_STATE b;
1944 char *buf;
1945 yy_size_t n;
1946 yy_size_t i;
1947
1948 /* Get memory for full buffer, including space for trailing EOB's. */
1949 n = (yy_size_t) (_yybytes_len + 2);
1950 buf = (char *) yyalloc( n );
1951 if ( ! buf )
1952 YY_FATAL_ERROR( "out of dynamic memory in yy_scan_bytes()" );
1953
1954 for ( i = 0; i < _yybytes_len; ++i )
1955 buf[i] = yybytes[i];
1956
1957 buf[_yybytes_len] = buf[_yybytes_len+1] = YY_END_OF_BUFFER_CHAR;
1958
1959 b = yy_scan_buffer( buf, n );
1960 if ( ! b )
1961 YY_FATAL_ERROR( "bad buffer in yy_scan_bytes()" );
1962
1963 /* It's okay to grow etc. this buffer, and we should throw it
1964 * away when we're done.
1965 */
1966 b->yy_is_our_buffer = 1;
1967
1968 return b;
1969}

2107int yylex_destroy (void)
2108{
2109
2110 /* Pop the buffer stack, destroying each element. */
2111 while(YY_CURRENT_BUFFER){
2112 yy_delete_buffer( YY_CURRENT_BUFFER );
2113 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE = NULL;
2114 yypop_buffer_state();
2115 }
2116

2118 yyfree((yy_buffer_stack) );
2119 (yy_buffer_stack) = NULL;

2122 * yylex() is called, initialization will occur. */
2123 yy_init_globals( );
